\f0\fs30 \cf0 Northampton has about 57% tree canopy coverage overall. Coverage varies widely by ward, from 75% in Ward 6A to 16% in Ward 3A. Ward 3B is near the bottom with 24% coverage in 2021. Tree canopy in 3B is declining - from 2011 to 2021, Ward 3B lost 6 acres of trees. \
\
The development proposed for 8 View Ave removes 29 significant trees, with diameters from 20\'94 to 47\'94, and untold numbers of non-significant trees with diameter less than 20\'94. This will lead to an overall loss of more than one acre of tree canopy. This is twice the size the lot near Walgreens that was recently cleared by Eversource, and a significant loss of canopy coverage.\
